text: Hi guys,
You're welcome to the Future Tech, Of course, We’ve showcased a lot of amazing devices
on this channel, but today’s video takes things a few steps further.
We will be talking about 10 new extraordinary gadgets you can buy right now without regrets.
Stay tuned to the end of the video, and do not forget to hit the notification bell.
Lodge Solar Powered Speakers
A team of audio engineers who would love to extend the experience of quality audio outdoors
came up with the Lodge speaker as the first truly wireless speaker created to live outside
all year round.
No, you don't have to be worried about being affected by the rain or other weather conditions;
Lodge was designed to be weatherproof, coupled with 180 square inches of chip and shatterproof
solar panels to keep the system protected and charged.
Unlike other speakers with similar audio quality, you don't have to worry about plugging in
to charge; its built-in solar panel ensures it remains charged within a short time - This
Gives you the freedom to carry your speaker with you anywhere to enjoy a truly clear,
dynamic and immersive audio output.
The system is easy to install; all it takes is mounting the speaker on the stake you must
have fixed at your favorite spot
Priced at 210$, The battery lasts up to 15 hours on a single charge.
Kat loco
Featured on several platforms, KAT VR is ready to take VR to another level with these virtual
reality gear.
The designers created Loco as a foot-based VR locomotion system that would give users
total control of their lower body - Now, you can physically control all activities such
as jumping, running, or walking.
Its small wireless sensors provide decoupled head and body directions by giving you the
freedom to use your hands to shoot while moving in different directions.
Granting you access to an immersive experience of controlling your body directions with your
feet reduces motion sickness and gets rid of space limitations.
Integrated with wireless connection capacities, you are expected to derive an ultimate user
experience from each session.
You can decide to switch to cruise control for navigation around the Virtual world.
Its battery is super durable and can last up to 10 hours on a single charge.
Kat loco cost 268$.
Segway SuperScooter GT1
Segway just introduced a super scooter that claims to be the perfect combination of speed,
performance, and innovation you can ever ask for.
Riders get to enjoy the ultimate riding experience by selecting from the six modes made available
to take users from 0 to 30 meters per hour, the sturdy frames, the powerful motor, and
the suspension system.
Its 1,512 watt-hours high-performance battery coupled with a HeatFlux Multi-layer Cooling
System gives the SuperScooter the capacity to reach a range of up to 55.9 miles, and
the full control is all yours with the advanced braking system.
Made with safety in mind, the super scooter was built with 900 Lumens LED front light,
LED daytime running light, and turning signal lights in the front and rear of the scooter.
Priced at $3499, the super scooter comes with two tubeless tires with a self-repair seal
inside to withstand punctures without leaking.
Kindly take a moment to hit the like button, and do not forget to subscribe to the channel
if you haven't.
Kyan
Kyan by smart solutions is a 360-degree foldable Slim Magnetic Phone Stand with no limit to
where you place or use it.
As an intelligent and flexible compact phone stand, compatible with Android, iPhone, or
tablets, you can use the stand on any surface to enjoy a hands-free experience while driving
or doing other kinds of stuff.
You can adjust the metal frame to suit your best angle of view - it could be turning your
phone horizontally or vertically or adjusting the height.
While on your Facetime Calls, Zoom meetings or Skype, or even creating content, you can
be assured of your phone being held securely
Designed to be simple compared to other stands, Kyan is a truly wireless stand with no charging
ports.
Kyan is priced at 25$
B-PIX4 LED Backpack
BIOSLED wants to give the users of this innovative backpack a different vibe from what typical
backpacks do.
B-PIX4 Led backpack expresses your personality as a whole with the dynamic display function,
which, when turned on, the hidden built-in screen of the backpack will light up.
The designers of the B-PIX4 LED said they used display panels with high-end self-luminous
RGB full-color LED lamp beads with a high resolution to display more explicit and more
attractive pictures and animations.
You can customize the text, pictures, and gif animations to your choice, create themes
that match your mood, and play them with the LED space app control
The backpack has endless uses - it serves stylish personal purposes and attracts public
attention to your business or for a campaign.
B-PIX4 LED Backpack costs $269
Pixy
Snapchat has just revealed its first selfie drone called Pixy to give users shots or recordings
with the best resolution.
The portable device has cameras on the front and bottom to capture 2.7K resolution videos
and 12 MP photos, plus users can apply some integrated effects.
With a USB C charging port, a user can record five to eight flights on a single charge and
wirelessly transfer snaps captured to your Snapchat memories.
Pixy costs 249.99$
Coolper
Here is another functional device by smart solutions.
You know it can be pretty frustrating to have your newly prepared coffee turning cold within
a few minutes or your milkshake melting.
COOLPER was created to serve as an intelligent cooling and heating device for effective and
rapid heat transfer.
An assembly of world-class Peltier thermoelectric silent semiconductor technology gives it the
power to maintain your beverages at the perfect temperature without needing a refrigerator
or heater.
The engineers promised that the silicon non-slip tabletop ensures stable positioning, and the
airtight silicone cup lid guarantees 100 percent leakproof even when you hit bumps or potholes.
Putting vehicle owners into consideration, there is a retractable base to match all vehicle
cup holders so you can as well keep your beverages cool or warm even in the car.
Priced at 49$, coolper is your perfect companion.
HUUPE
Huupe is a smart basketball hoop that gives you the chance to play basketball indoors
or outdoors and enjoy a more interactive and competitive gaming session.
With claims to be the first smart basketball hoop, Huupe comes with a high-definition screen
that allows you to train like a pro with the series of training sessions made available
for you.
Despite being a smart basketball hoop, the huupe is weatherproof to withstand adverse
conditions both indoors and outdoors, and you can stream contents from your phone to
the huupe.
With the help of a built-in sensor, the device also tracks all your activities on the court,
including your shooting percentage, swishes, trajectory, position, agility, and others
Also, you can schedule a live session with your favorite trainer and watch your progress
among thousands of other players.
While playing, you can stream content from the intuitive mobile app to watch your favorite
shows while you play.
Huupe is priced at $3995.
AiFeet
To solve the inconvenience that comes with typical insoles built with materials that
don't provide wearers with the necessary comfort they deserve, Aifeet was designed to consider
contours unique to everyone's feet thoroughly.
The Aifeet insole is custom-made to properly fit your feet and add comfort to every stride
or kick.
With the intuitive appLuxCare advanced technology, your foot gets measured with its details when
you scan it, and the designers use 3D printing technology to customize your perfect insole.
Each AiFeet insole is made of high-performance, elastic resin material, which has high elasticity,
more tenacity, and resilience to absorb shock and protect your ankles and knees.
The lattice structure of the material used is breathable and reduces humidity with a
dynamic airflow which drives out any form of moisture.
Priced at 20$, Aifeet is easy to clean and dries off within a few minutes.
LifeStraw Mission
The LifeStraw Mission gravity-powered water purifier removes 99.9999% of bacteria, protozoa,
viruses, microplastic dirt, and sediments from any water source - streams, rivers, and
the like.
You use the durable bag made of TPU laminated nylon to fetch water and hang the bag to access
the purified water.
Available in two sizes, the strap on the bag makes it easy to transport around.
Lifestraw mission comes with an ultrafiltration membrane to filter all forms of physical or
microbial contamination in the water; it also features a quick-connect hose as well as an
integrated backwash system to wash the bag when necessary.
The replaceable membrane ultrafilter can purify up to 18,000 liters of water.
On your next adventure, you can be assured of drinking purified water with no risk.
Lifestraw mission is approximated to cost 98$.
